#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:17
msgid ""
"One of the features that an IDE must surely have is the ability to manage "
"the various projects that a developer or publisher works on. Being able to "
"select the project to work on once NvChad is open, without the need to type "
"commands in the *statusline* to achieve the goal. This saves time and allows "
"for simplified management in the case of a large number of projects."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:19
msgid ""
"Using [charludo/projectmgr.nvim](https://github.com/charludo/projectmgr."
"nvim) will integrate this functionality. The plugin provides excellent "
"integration with `Telescope` and some interesting additional features such "
"as the ability to synchronize a *git* repository when opening the *project*."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:21
msgid ""
"The plugin also tracks the status of the editor when it closes allowing you "
"to have, when you next open it, all the pages you were working on."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:22
#, no-wrap
msgid "Plugin installation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:25
msgid ""
"To install the plugin you will need to edit the **custom/plugins.lua** file "
"by adding the following block of code:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (lua)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:26
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{\n"
"    \"charludo/projectmgr.nvim\",\n"
"    lazy = false, -- important!\n"
"},\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:34
#, no-wrap
msgid "Once you have saved the file, the plugin will be available for installation. To install it open *lazy.nvim* with the command `:Lazy` and type <kbd>I</kbd>. Once the installation finishes you will have to exit the editor and reopen it to have it read the new configuration you entered.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:36
msgid ""
"The plugin provides a single command `:ProjectMgr` that opens an interactive "
"buffer from which you can perform all operations by using keyboard "
"shortcuts. When first opened, the buffer will be empty as this screenshot "
"shows:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:38
msgid "![ProjectMgr Init](./images/projectmgr_init.png)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:39
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using the Project Manager"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:42
#, no-wrap
msgid "All operations are performed with the <kbd>Ctrl</kbd> key followed by a letter (e.g. `<C-a`), while the `<CR>` key corresponds to the <kbd>Enter</kbd> key.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:44
msgid "The following table shows all available operations"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:52
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Key     | Operation                                       |\n"
"|-------- | ----------------------------------------------- |\n"
"| `<CR>`  | Opens the project under the cursor              |\n"
"| `<C-a>` | Adds a project through an interactive procedure |\n"
"| `<C-d>` | Delete a project                                |\n"
"| `<C-e>` | Change project settings                         |\n"
"| `<C-q>` | Close buffer                                    |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:54
#, no-wrap
msgid "To add your first project you will need to use the combination <kbd>Ctrl</kbd> + <kbd>a</kbd> which will open an interactive menu in the *statusline*. In this example a clone of the Rocky Linux documentation saved in **~/lab/rockydocs/documentation** will be used.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:56
msgid "The first question will ask you for the name of the project:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:58
#, no-wrap
msgid "> Project Name: documentation\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:60
msgid "It will follow the project path:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:62
#, no-wrap
msgid "> Project Path: ~/lab/rockydocs/documentation/\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:64
msgid ""
"This is followed by the ability to set commands to be run when opening and "
"closing the project. These commands refer to those executable in the editor "
"and not to the **bash** language."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:66
msgid ""
"You have, for example, the possibility to open contextually when opening the "
"editor a side buffer with *NvimTree* with the command `NvimTreeToggle`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:68
#, no-wrap
msgid "> Startup Command (optional): NvimTreeToggle\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:70
msgid "Or to run a command before closing the editor."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:72
#, no-wrap
msgid "> Exit Command (optional):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:74
msgid ""
"Commands should be entered by omitting the colon `:` used to run the same "
"commands in the *statusline.*"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:76
#, no-wrap
msgid "Once the configuration is finished, your project will be available in the buffer. To open it, select it and press <kbd>Enter</kbd>.\n"
