#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:78
msgid "![ProjectMgr Add](./images/projectmgr_add.png)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:80
msgid ""
"As you can see from the screenshot in the **Config & Info** section, the "
"plugin has recognized the folder as managed by *Git* and provides us with "
"some information about it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:82
#, no-wrap
msgid "Editing a project is done with <kbd>Ctrl</kbd> + <kbd>e</kbd> and consists of a new interactive loop, while any deletion is accomplished with the combination <kbd>Ctrl</kbd> + <kbd>d</kbd>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:83
#, no-wrap
msgid "Additional functions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:86
msgid ""
"The plugin provides some additional functions specified in the [dedicated "
"section](https://github.com/charludo/projectmgr.nvim#%EF%B8%8F-"
"configuration). The most interesting ones are the ability to synchronize a "
"git repository when opening the project and the ability to store the status "
"of the editor when closing it. Both features are already present in the "
"default configuration file, although, the functionality regarding *Git* is "
"disabled."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:88
msgid ""
"To add repository synchronization when opening projects you will need to add "
"the following code to the initial plugin configuration:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (lua)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:89
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"config = function()\n"
"    require(\"projectmgr\").setup({\n"
"        autogit = {\n"
"            enabled = true,\n"
"            command = \"git pull --ff-only >> .git/fastforward.log 2>&1\",\n"
"        },\n"
"    })\n"
"end,\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:101
msgid ""
"As you can see from the code the `require(\"projectmgr\").setup` function is "
"called, which allows you to override the default settings. Anything you set "
"inside it will change how it works."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:103
msgid ""
"The `git pull --ff-only` command performs a *fast forward* synchronization "
"of the repository, downloading only those files that have no conflicts and "
"can be updated without intervention on your part."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:105
msgid ""
"The result of the command also is directed to the file **.git/fastforward."
"log** to prevent it from being displayed on the terminal where NvChad is "
"running and to have a synchronization history available."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:107
msgid ""
"Also provided is the option to save the session when it closes. This allows "
"you to return to the pages you were working on by selecting the project and "
"opening it again."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (lua)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:108
#, no-wrap
msgid "session = { enabled = true, file = \"Session.vim\" },\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:113
msgid ""
"This option is enabled by default but it writes the **Session.vim** file to "
"the *root* directory of the project and this is not desirable in the case of "
"Rocky Linux documentation. In this example, it is saved in the `.git` folder "
"which is not under version control."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:115
msgid ""
"Adjust the path of **Session.vim** and **fastforward.log** according to your "
"needs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:117
msgid ""
"Once the changes are complete, your configuration should look as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (lua)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:118
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{\n"
"    \"charludo/projectmgr.nvim\",\n"
"    lazy = false, -- important!\n"
"    config = function()\n"
"        require(\"projectmgr\").setup({\n"
"            autogit = {\n"
"                enabled = true,\n"
"                command = \"git pull --ff-only > .git/fastforward.log 2>&1\",\n"
"            },\n"
"            session = { enabled = true, file = \".git/Session.vim\" },\n"
"        })\n"
"    end,\n"
"},\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:135
msgid ""
"Now each time you open your projects, updated files will be automatically "
"downloaded from the Git repository and you will have the latest files you "
"were working on open in the editor ready for editing."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:137
msgid "!!! Warning"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:139
#, no-wrap
msgid "    Open files in NvChad's saved session buffers are not automatically updated.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:141
msgid ""
"To check if the open files do not match those updated from the repository "
"you can use the `:checktime` command, which checks if the files open in the "
"editor have been modified outside NvChad and alerts you to the need to "
"update the buffers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:142
#, no-wrap
msgid "Mapping"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:145
msgid ""
"To speed up the opening of your projects, you can create a keyboard shortcut "
"to put in your mapping in **/custom/mapping.lua**. An example might be:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (lua)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:146
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"-- Projects\n"
"M.projects = {\n"
"  n = {\n"
"    [\"<leader>fp\"] = { \"<cmd> ProjectMgr<CR>\", \"Open Projects\"}\n"
"    },\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:156
#, no-wrap
msgid "With the editor in the **NORMAL** state you can open the project manager with the combination <kbd>Space</kbd> + <kbd>f</kbd> followed by <kbd>p</kbd>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:157
#, no-wrap
msgid "Conclusions and final thoughts"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:160
msgid ""
"As the number of projects you are working on increases, it might be useful "
"to have a tool to help you manage them all. This plugin will allow you to "
"speed up your work by reducing the time it takes to access the files you "
"need to edit."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:161
msgid ""
"We should also point out the excellent integration with `Telescope` which "
"makes project management very functional."
msgstr ""
